CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 28, 1961, p. 32, reads: "Touchdown Schenley! - This was the big moment, last week, when underdog Schenley High had the wagering factions dizzy...by way of a touchdown against mighty Westinghouse High, in the first of their hectic encounter, to take a 6-0 lead into the halftime intermission.  Westinghouse roared back to win, 14-6."
TitMainTitle: Schenley and Westinghouse High School football game, with players #67, #63, #54, at Westinghouse field
